attributes.magic: PE32+ executable (GUI) x86-64, for MS Windows

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a malicious loader/stager designed to execute shellcode in memory. Key indicators include: 1) Anti-analysis/anti-sandbox timing checks in the 'main' function using 'clock' and 'Sleep' to verify execution speed. 2) Heavy obfuscation of a payload through fragmentation into 40+ strings. 3) A multi-stage decoding process involving Base64 decoding (function 'oBSGMKR') and Hex-to-byte conversion (function 'zhrRs'). 4) The allocation of executable memory with PAGE_EXECUTE_READWRITE (RWX) permissions via 'VirtualAlloc', followed by a 'memmove' and direct execution of the decoded shellcode. The presence of 'mark_section_writable' further suggests self-modifying code or manual relocation typical of malware.
